CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, December 23, 1961, pg. 1 reads: "Honoring Past Matron - Members of the Booker T. Washington Court 21, Daughters of Sphinx, honored their past matron, Dt. Eva Carter, and Illustrious Patron, Noble Rosella Carlo, recently, during a reception at Hill City. Guests, seated at the table are: Dts. Louise Green, Lula Matthews, Eva Chatman, Eva Carter and Noble Rosella Carlo honorees; Mrs. Mable Carlo, Dt. Anna Williams, George Dudley, A.G.P. and the Rev. J.R.Cannon.  Dt. Albertine Sellers and Noble James Folson are standing. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Group portrait, seated from left: Louise Green, Lula Matthews, Eva Chatman, Eva Carter and Noble Rosella Carlo, honorees; Mable Carlo, Anna Williams, George Dudley, and Rev. J.R. Cannon; standing: Albertine Sellers and James Folson, gathered around rectangular banquet table in Hill City for Booker T. Washington Court No. 21, Daughters of Sphinx reception, another version
